# Next.js Feature Architecture Rule

## Folder Structure (Feature First)

- Organize domain code under `features/<feature-name>/`.
- Each feature must contain: `components`, `types`, `view`, `data`, `constants`.
- Keep route files lean; compose feature views in routes.

Example:

```txt
features/auth/
  components/
  types/
  view/
  data/
  constants/
```

## View Composition Pattern

- Build full UI composition inside `features/<feature>/view/*View.tsx`.
- Route files in `app/**/page.tsx` should import and render the feature view, not assemble large UI trees directly.

## Next.js Best Practices

- Use App Router patterns (`layout.tsx`, `page.tsx`, server components by default).
- Keep client components minimal and only when interactivity is needed.
- Prefer colocated feature logic over global shared folders unless truly reusable.

## SEO and Metadata

- Every route segment should define metadata via `export const metadata` or `generateMetadata`.
- Include meaningful `title`, `description`, and canonical intent where relevant.
- Use semantic HTML landmarks and proper heading hierarchy (`h1` once per page intent).
- For multilingual pages, localize metadata (title/description) per language and keep route intent consistent.

## TypeScript Standards

- Define domain models in `features/<feature>/types`.
- Avoid `any`; prefer explicit interfaces, unions, and utility types.
- Type component props, API payloads, and data-layer return values.
- Keep types close to the feature unless shared across multiple domains.
- Use explicit language types (for example `type AppLanguage = "en" | "hi"`) and typed dictionaries for translation content.

## Design System Enforcement (DESIGN-mistral.ai.md)

- Follow warm palette tokens (ivory, cream, amber, orange, mistral black).
- Keep font weight mostly `400`; hierarchy by scale, spacing, and color.
- Use sharp corners (near-zero radius) and warm golden shadow treatment.
- Avoid cool brand colors and overly rounded UI patterns.

## i18n and Media Best Practices

- Store UI copy in typed dictionaries under `features/<feature>/data`, not inline in JSX.
- Pass translated content via props from the view layer to components.
- Language switchers must be controlled by typed state in `view/*View.tsx`.
- Hero background images should use low-opacity overlays to preserve text readability and warm theme consistency.
